BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Hibernate in complex projects – Can we be a little faster?
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20210218T190000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20210218T210000
UID:https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/276178510/@community-events
DESCRIPTION:🔗 https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/276178510/\n\nH
 ibernate is the de-facto standard for persisting data in a relational data
 base. It provides excellent developer productivity and is so easy to use t
 hat you can learn it within a few hours.\nThat changes as soon as your app
 lication needs to handle a huge amount of data or if you want to guarantee
  very short response times. Features and concepts that work perfectly fine
  for smaller applications start to become a burden that slows down your ap
 plication.\nBut that doesn’t have to be the case for your application. H
 ibernate is a great fit for complex projects with high-performance require
 ments. You only need to know which features to use and which you should be
 tter avoid.\nDuring this talk\, I will show you how to get the most out of
  your Hibernate-based persistence layer. By following these recommendation
 s\, you will be able to enjoy Hibernate’s developer productivity and pro
 vide a blazingly fast experience to your users.\nMore information on http:
 //www.bordeauxjug.org\n\nCommunauté: bordeauxjug\n💻 Événement en lig
 ne
TZID:Europe/Paris
URL:https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/276178510/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Don't fear outdated caches -- change data capture to the rescue! 
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20210121T190000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20210121T210000
UID:https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/275773605/@community-events
DESCRIPTION:🔗 https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/275773605/\n\nT
 he saying goes that there are only two hard things in Computer Science: ca
 che invalidation and naming things.\nWell\, turns out the first is solved 
 actually \;)\nCome and join us for a session to hear not about one\, but t
 wo popular open-source projects.\nFirst\, Infinispan\, an in-memory distri
 buted data store and cache\, which is elastically scalable\, highly availa
 bility and fault-tolerant.\nThen\, Debezium\, a change data capture (CDC) 
 platform for a variety of databases\, such as MySQL\, PostgreSQL and Mongo
 DB.\nAfter an overview of the key use cases and capabilities of the two pr
 ojects\, we'll explore in a demo how you can combine Debezium and Infinisp
 an for even greater awesomeness:\nHow to keep your cache automatically up-
 to-date after data changes via Debezium and CDC\nHow to read denormalized 
 views of your data with plain key look-ups from an Infinispan cluster clos
 e by\nHow to propagate cache updates between clusters using cross-site rep
 lication\nAll this driven by Quarkus and connected via Apache Kafka. Bring
  your questions and ideas so we can discuss and exchange about the potenti
 al of these open-source projects in the data space!\nMore information on h
 ttp://bordeauxjug.org\n\nCommunauté: bordeauxjug\n💻 Événement en lig
 ne
TZID:Europe/Paris
URL:https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/275773605/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:3 easy improvements in your microservices architecture
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20201217T190000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20201217T210000
UID:https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/275058477/@community-events
DESCRIPTION:🔗 https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/275058477/\n\nW
 hile a microservices architecture is more scalable than a monolith\, it ha
 s a direct hit on performance.\nTo cope with that\, one performance improv
 ement is to set up a cache. It can be configured for database access\, for
  REST calls or just to store session state across a cluster of server node
 s. In this demo-based talk\, I’ll show how Hazelcast In-Memory Data Grid
  can help you in each one of those areas and how to configure it.\nHint: i
 t’s much easier than one would expect\nPlus d'informations sur le site h
 ttp://www.bordeauxjug.org/\n\nCommunauté: bordeauxjug\n💻 Événement e
 n ligne
TZID:Europe/Paris
URL:https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/275058477/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Plug-in Architectures for Java with Layrry and the Java Module Sys
 tem
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20201119T190000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20201119T210000
UID:https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/274507026/@community-events
DESCRIPTION:🔗 https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/274507026/\n\nT
 he Java Module System lays the foundation for building modularized applica
 tions on the JVM. It doesn’t concern itself though with resolving module
  versions and obtaining modules from repositories.\nThis is where Layrry c
 omes in: an API and launcher for modularized Java applications which takes
  a descriptor of the module layer(s) to assemble\, fetches the modules and
  starts up the application.\nJoin us for this session and learn how to:\nB
 uild Java applications using layers\, e.g. providing isolation between dif
 ferent versions of one module. Use jbang to launch your layered apps in no
  time. Create plug-in based rich-client applications using JavaFX and Layr
 ry\, allowing to – dynamically reconfigure and update your layer hierarc
 hy\, no restarts required. Create your own customized Layrry launcher if n
 eeded\nThis session is code-centered\, be ready to see the Java Module Sys
 tem\, Layrry\, and JavaFX in action!\n-- Session in English / Session en a
 nglais\n\nCommunauté: bordeauxjug\n💻 Événement en ligne
TZID:Europe/Paris
URL:https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/274507026/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Mieux maîtriser la performance applicative avec la librairie de t
 est QuickPerf
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20201015T190000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20201015T210000
UID:https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/273864451/@community-events
DESCRIPTION:🔗 https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/273864451/\n\nL
 a performance est souvent considérée de manière tardive\, voire ignoré
 e\, dans le cycle de développement applicatif. Ceci induit un risque de d
 écouvrir tardivement que l'application est lente ou inutilisable.\nVous a
 llez découvrir comment la librairie de test QuickPerf (https://github.com
 /quick-perf/quickperf) permet de supprimer sans beaucoup d'effort et au pl
 us tôt des goulets d'étranglement de performance.\nSi votre application 
 possède déjà des tests de performance\, comme des tirs de charge\, vous
  verrez comment les tests QuickPerf peuvent les compléter et vous faire g
 agner du temps\nPlus d'informations sur le site de votre JUG (http://www.b
 ordeauxjug.org)\n\nCommunauté: bordeauxjug\n💻 Événement en ligne
TZID:Europe/Paris
URL:https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/273864451/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Spring Boot Loves K8s
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Paris:20200910T190000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Paris:20200910T210000
UID:https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/272912566/@community-events
DESCRIPTION:🔗 https://www.meetup.com/bordeauxjug/events/272912566/\n\nC
 ontainers and platforms are now part of the developer’s toolbox\;\nit’
 s sometimes hard to standardize the containerization and deployment of Spr
 ing Boot applications in your organization\, while still remaining flexibl
 e.\nSpring Boot 2.3 is out now with new features for containers and Kubern
 etes.\nDuring this session\, Stephane and Brian will share with you the Sp
 ring Boot 2.3 features that will help you to:\n- Easily create optimized c
 ontainer images of your application\n- Simplify and standardize your CI/CD
  pipeline\n- Manage the lifecycle of your application in a Kubernetes envi
 ronment with Probes\nAnd more!\nPlus d'informations sur le site de votre J
 UG (http://www.bordeauxjug.org)\n\nCommunauté: bordeauxjug\n💻 Événem
 ent en ligne
